  "prompt": "How is the placement at IIHMR Jaipur?",
  "response": "IIHMR (Indian Institute of Health Management Research) in Jaipur is known for good placements, particularly in healthcare management and related fields. Here are some key points about placements:\n\n1. Placement Percentage:\n- Usually around 80-90% of students get placed\n- Many students get offers from leading healthcare organizations, hospitals, pharmaceutical companies, and consulting firms\n\n2. Average Salary:\n- Typically ranges between \u20b94-6 lakhs per annum\n- Some top performers may get higher packages\n\n3. Recruiters:\n- Apollo Hospitals\n- Fortis Healthcare\n- Max Healthcare\n- Cipla\n- Novartis\n- WHO\n- McKinsey\n- Deloitte\n- Ernst & Young\n- Various state health departments and NGOs\n\n4. Placement Support:\n- Dedicated placement cell\n- Industry interface\n- Internship opportunities\n- Resume building workshops\n- Interview preparation\n\n5. Specializations:\n- Healthcare Management\n- Pharmaceutical Management\n- Hospital Administration\n- Public Health Management\n\nWhile these details provide a general overview, specific placement statistics can vary year to year. It's recommended to directly contact the institute for the most current placement information.",
